Description: Fragment of oval handle to sharp turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine light pink-brown. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '411' and '441'. Name Aratophanes. Probably from same die as the worn Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR 405.42.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (3)
